 Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas, Palermo","front",[],[153,154,154,155,156,157,158],"Kaibel, 1890, IG","Supplementum epigraphicum graecum, 1923-","Pugliese Carratelli, 1956, Silloge dell' epigrafi acrensi","Manganaro, 1981, L'oracolo di Maie per una carestia in territorio siracusano","Manganaro, 1994, Iscrizioni, epigrafi ed epigrammi in Greco della Sicilia orientale di epoca romana","Brugnone, 2014, Divinità femminili ad Akrai",[160,161,161,162,163,164,165],"Q2SBPG9F","F2GG87EQ","PJDRZH66","4RHZUP7V","532NF7SV","J9ISUCNR",[167,168,169,13,17,21,170,171,172,173,174,175,176,142],"isic001040","i.sicily inscription 001040",{"_":10},"acrae","palazzolo acreide","italy","sicily","palermo","museo archeologico regionale antonino salinas","ancient greek","Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, edition source:",{"file":179,"uri":179,"title":180,"status":181,"editionAuthor":11,"type":182,"objectType":186,"material":188,"condition":192,"layoutDesc":193,"handNote":197,"date":333,"places":336,"geo":339,"country":130,"region":131,"settlement":341,"repository":342,"idno":345,"textLang":347,"facsimile":349,"provenance":118,"letterHeights":354,"publications":355,"zotero":362,"keywords":369,"html":375},"ISic002754","I.Sicily inscription 002754",{"_":10},{"_":183,"ana":184,"ref":185},"oracle","#function.oracle","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/429.html",{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":187},"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":189,"ana":190,"ref":191},"limestone","#material.stone.limestone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html","",{"layout":194},{"p":195,"rs":196,"damage":192},"The left margin of the text is carefully justified, but the right margin is very uneven, with several extensive vacats at line end.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":198,"dimensions":326},[199,200],"Regular small letters of generally consistent size, deeply cut with pronounced terminal serifs on some strokes. Alpha is broad with straight bar, occasional extension of apex; beta appears open with rounded but not fully circular equal loops; epsilon has shorter middle bar, and upper and lower strokes often curve outwards at the ends; theta is ovoid with complete horizontal bar; kappa has short, equal length tails; mu has middle stroks joining well above the line; nu has the lower right angle above the line with shorter right vertical stroke; omicron is smaller and above the line; pi has shorter right vertical; rho is closed with generally circular eye; sigma has upper and lower horizontals curving slightly outwards at the ends, and the middle strokes often form into a single curving stroke; phi has a rounded eye, with the vertical extended, up to 17mm; psi has extended vertical and straight arms; omega is small, rounded, above the line, and open, with generally horizontal tail strokes.",{"_":201,"ref":202},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                