":389,"damage":192},"Remains of three lines of Greek letters, with vacat below; the first line (damaged) is larger than the second and third\n                                    \n                                \t\n\t\t\t",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":391,"dimensions":392},"Somewhat irregular, deep cut letters with pronounced terminal serfis. Lunate sigma and epsilon, xsi formed somewhat after the fashion of the numeral 3, omicron in line 2 tiny.",[393,395,399],{"type":103,"l":104,"from":105,"to":105,"h":394,"unit":106},"incomplete",{"type":103,"l":396,"from":110,"to":397,"h":398,"unit":106},"Lines 2-3","line3","8-10",{"type":108,"l":109,"from":105,"to":110,"h":332,"unit":106},{"_":401,"notBefore":402,"notAfter":403,"precision":115},"1st — 3rd century CE?",1,300,[405,408],{"_":406,"type":119,"ref":407},"Syracusae","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462503",{"_":341,"type":123,"ref":409},"http://sws.geonames.org/2523083",[411],[412,413],37.08415,15.27628,{"_":343,"role":135,"ref":344},{"_":141,"mainLang":142,"languages":416},[141],{"n":145,"url":418,"height":419,"width":420,"desc":421,"surfaceType":150},"ISic003128_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana",[],[154,156],[161,163],[426,427,428,381,17,21,429,373,172,173,373,374,176,142],"isic003128","i.sicily inscription 003128",{"_":10},"syracusae",{"file":431,"uri":431,"title":432,"status":433,"editionAuthor":11,"type":434,"objectType":435,"material":439,"condition":192,"layoutDesc":440,"handNote":444,"date":525,"places":528,"geo":531,"country":130,"region":131,"settlement":341,"repository":533,"idno":534,"textLang":536,"facsimile":538,"provenance":118,"letterHeights":541,"publications":542,"zotero":543,"keywords":544,"html":375},"ISic003367","I.Sicily inscription 003367",{"_":10},{"_":183,"ana":184,"ref":185},{"_":436,"ana":437,"ref":438},"stele","#object.stele","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/250",{"_":189,"ana":190,"ref":191},{"layout":441},{"p":442,"rs":443,"damage":192},"The text is neatly laid out with a clear left margin on a single field below the moulding; divisions in the text at lines 5-6 and 25-26 are marked by paragraphoi.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":445,"dimensions":519},[446,447],"Letters are regular and deeply cut, with slightly prounced serifs at the end of strokes. Alpha is broad with straight bar, and occasional tendency to apex at the top; beta has equal sized, closed, shallow loops; epsilon has shorter middle bar and slightly outward pointing top and bottom bars; zeta is formed by a vertical with horizontals top and bottom; theta is slightly ovoid in form, with a complete cross bar; kappa has short, equal length tails; Mu has slightly inward leaning first and final strokes, with the middle strokes meeting well above the middle of the line; nu has a shorter right hand stroke, with the lower angle above the line; omicron is small and mid-line; Pi has a slightly shorter right hand vertical; rho has small closed eye, of varying form (rounded or elongated); sigma has slightly outward facing top and bottom storkes and the middle strokes are sometimes rounded at the join; upsilon has shallow spreading upper strokes; phi has a rounded eye, with extended vertical stroke; chi is consistnly slightly larger than other characters; omega open, slightly smaller and above the line, with horizontal tails. A horizontal stroke is visible above and the left of the first letter of lines 6 and 26.",{"_":448,"ref":449},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                             